description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Moorfields NHS Foundation Trust – Bank Ophthalmic Technician &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking motivated and trained Ophthalmic Technician to be part of the specialised teams at Moorfields Eye Hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Looking for flexible shifts to suit your availability or lines of work?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Why not join the Moorfields bank?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will get first choice of shifts suited to your availability and skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shifts will be available between 8am and 17.30pm.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PURPOSE OF THE JOB&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To perform visual field assessments on a wide variety of patients&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To capture images of the retina using specialised equipment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To measure visual acuity and accurately test intra ocular pressure&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be responsible for your own case load, prioritising and accepting urgent referrals when&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;necessary&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To ensure patients are received in a sympathetic and courteous manner and that cultural difference is catered for&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To present findings to the medics and other health care professionals&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MAIN DUTIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To perform visual field tests using own initiative but with supervision if needed&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To perform retinal tomography measurements using corrective lenses as required&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To measure visual acuities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To measure intra ocular pressures&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To measure patients’ spectacle corrections and interpret this information to select the correct lens for visual field testing&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To ensure patients attending the Glaucoma Monitoring Unit understand the new pathway&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To decide on the most appropriate test to perform by applying the protocols and procedures agreed by the Orthoptist and to seek advice when necessary&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To produce high quality readings by using high levels of concentration&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Help in the daily maintenance of the equipment and trial lenses&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-VA ( Visual acute)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- OCT&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- 6 months NHS experience in a similar role&lt;/p&gt;
